# arpeggio range cap: "The maximum allowed range is 0.8 (8 octaves). Higher
# values will be capped to that." Here range is set to 1.0 (10V), which must be
# capped to 0.8 -> 96 semitones. With direction=1 the arpeggio starts at the
# highest allowed note; in C Lydian the highest pc at or below semi 96 is
# semi 96 (C, since 96/12 = 8 octaves) = 0.8 V exactly.
# Were the range NOT capped, the top note would be semi 120 (1.0), so this
# pins the cap.
patch <<<
[arpeggio]
    clock     = I1
    output    = O1
    pitch     = 0
    range     = 1.0
    direction = 1
>>>
@1 set I1 1
@1 expect O1 0.8 tol 1e-5
